# CAOS_QLAB — environment template. COPY to .env for the OPTIONAL real-hardware lane only.
#
# The public app is fully STATIC: the live lane runs a JavaScript simulator in the browser and the
# precompute lane runs locally; NEITHER needs a secret. You only need tokens if you opt into the
# real-hardware lane (scripts/precompute with --backend ibm|braket|azure) to run a case on a real QPU
# and commit the returned counts as a trace. Real tokens live ONLY in the CAOS_MANAGE vault — never
# commit a populated .env (CI guards reject it).

# --- IBM Quantum (free Open Plan: 10 min QPU / 28-day window on 156-qubit Heron r2) ---
# Get a token at https://quantum.cloud.ibm.com → API token.
QISKIT_IBM_TOKEN=
QISKIT_IBM_INSTANCE=        # optional CRN/instance for the IBM Quantum Platform channel

# --- AWS Braket (optional; per-task + per-shot billing) ---
# Standard AWS credentials + an S3 results bucket; configure via the AWS CLI, not here.
# AWS_BRAKET_S3_BUCKET=
# AWS_BRAKET_S3_PREFIX=qlab

# --- Azure Quantum (optional; $500 one-time credit) ---
# AZURE_QUANTUM_WORKSPACE=
# AZURE_QUANTUM_LOCATION=
# AZURE_QUANTUM_RESOURCE_GROUP=
